{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3147291,"name":"Bill Bagshaw","username":"BMLSS","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/b/e68b1a/{size}.png","created_at":"2023-02-17T03:56:18.449Z","cooked":"<p>We have finally moved on from CIM motors and we are newbies to Neos.  What is the best way to set up four Neos for an arcade drive differential drivetrain?  We are interested in getting the most out of whatever odometery we can get from the onboard encoders. Also- is brake mode recommended to help prevent sliding down a tipped charge station?</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":6,"updated_at":"2023-02-17T04:01:50.569Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":146,"reads":155,"readers_count":154,"score":761.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":427142,"topic_slug":"new-to-neo-drive-train-what-is-best-with-java-motor-group-or-leader-follower","display_username":"Bill Bagshaw","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":50591,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/new-to-neo-drive-train-what-is-best-with-java-motor-group-or-leader-follower/427142/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3147389,"name":"Elliot Scher","username":"Gandagorn","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/gandagorn/{size}/267112_2.png","created_at":"2023-02-17T11:18:22.801Z","cooked":"<p>Our team uses leader/followers and have never had any issues with them. We also put the motors in brake mode.</p>
<p>Here is our code if you’re interested: <a href="https://gitlab.com/ecscher84/2815-robot-2023" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Elliot Scher / 2815 Robot 2023 · GitLab</a></p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":6,"updated_at":"2023-02-17T11:18:22.801Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":137,"readers_count":136,"score":32.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":427142,"topic_slug":"new-to-neo-drive-train-what-is-best-with-java-motor-group-or-leader-follower","display_username":"Elliot Scher","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://gitlab.com/ecscher84/2815-robot-2023","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Elliot Scher / 2815 Robot 2023 · GitLab","clicks":40}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":49423,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"2815A (19-23) | 190M (23...)"},"post_url":"/t/new-to-neo-drive-train-what-is-best-with-java-motor-group-or-leader-follower/427142/2","custom_user_title":"2815A (19-23) | 190M (23...)","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3147553,"name":"Allen Nuttle","username":"nuttle","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/nuttle/{size}/124105_2.png","created_at":"2023-02-17T17:06:12.920Z","cooked":"<p>Leader/Follower is probably the way to go in nearly all scenarios.  Potentially, this saves some CAN bandwidth, and it ensures the motors are sharing the load at all times.  Motor group doesn’t support all of the closed-loop modes, so this also sets you up to use those.</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":6,"updated_at":"2023-02-17T17:06:12.920Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":105,"readers_count":104,"score":36.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":427142,"topic_slug":"new-to-neo-drive-train-what-is-best-with-java-motor-group-or-leader-follower","display_username":"Allen Nuttle","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":14283,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/new-to-neo-drive-train-what-is-best-with-java-motor-group-or-leader-follower/427142/3","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3147581,"name":"Bill Bagshaw","username":"BMLSS","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/b/e68b1a/{size}.png","created_at":"2023-02-17T18:13:40.359Z","cooked":"<p>Thank you both! We have decided to use this for our very first test of the drive train. I am not happy about the repetitiveness of the code, but I hope it it clear and correct for the team to build on.</p>
